  "title": "EEGEyeNet Dataset",
  "description": "EEGEyeNet is a simultaneous electroencephalography and eye-tracking dataset designed for eye movement prediction research. This BIDS-standardized version contains raw neurophysiological recordings from a single subject extracted from the larger EEGEyeNet dataset, enabling investigation of the neural correlates of oculomotor control and the relationship between brain activity and gaze dynamics.",
  "methods_description": "Data were collected simultaneously using electroencephalography (EEG) and eye-tracking technology. The study received ethical approval from the Institutional Review Board of Canton Zurich (BASEC-Nr. 2017-00226).",
